The rules for this game:

Roll a 100 sided die
If your roll is higher than the current king, you're the new king!
If your roll is equal or lower than the current king's number, the king's number is lowered by 5
You can't roll multiple times in a row
You can't roll if you're currently king
Invalid rolls do not count

alwaysmetara

Yup. 98
Btw, rolling a 10 10 sided dies is different from rolling a 100 sided one. I actually did a math problem on that once... since it's impossible to roll a sum of 1 on 10 ten sided dies, while on a 100 sided die, it's possible.
Also, the probability of rolling a sum of 100 on 10 ten sided dies is
1/10 * 1/10 * 1/10 * 1/10 * 1/10 *... 10 times, which is: 1/10000000000
which is much less than 1/100.
So if you use 10 ten sided dies in place of a 100 sided die, you have a much greater chance to roll a number close to 50, instead of an equal chance to roll any number between 1 and 100 inclusive.

Yes, you are king now.

The first "7" in your post, no matter where it is, is your attack force. Additional 5s or other valued dice (like 2 or 5) do not count even if you add them together.
If your attack force is more than the current king's defense force then you become king.
If your attack force is less than the current king's defense force then you subtract 5 from their defense force.
You cannot attack until at least one person has attacked before you.
